			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I had a horror story time with my 52 fire pet in the PoN last night, so I think I can suggest a few things.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I liked this pet, but I was scared for it's mana the entire time. It would run out and go into melee. That isn't right. Maybe the fire pet should work like the chanter pet in that it only goes into melee when the mage is attacked? Seriously, the pet going into melee is and has always been our one line of defense, can't just take it out. When u tell the pet to attack it should nuke, nuke, and nuke. When not attacking it should keep it's buffs on itself and possibly buff it's master (but we dont NEED that for him to be fixed).
<br />

<br />
One important thing, the damage shield should be innate like it used to be pre-50. It's a buff that it casts on itself, and that isn't right. Bad SoE.
<br />

<br />

<br />
It roots, which sucks. I would rather it snare, but at the same time, if it snared you would rely on that pet for the snare, and if I can't control him directly I dont want him to do that. I haven't run into any AoE dispells, but if it dispells everyone's buffs then that isn't right, and I don't know what the hell SoE was thinking. Cancel magic is one thing, aoe dispell is another. I would be happy if the fire pet just nuked, but then wouldn't we out damage people? Heh, good, it's the way a wizard pet should be. Don't give our pet a wizard's utility if you don't give him the know how to use it, or a way to let us control that utility. If he can't have the utility then I like him just fine as a backup nuker. Raiding pet, anyone?
<br />

<br />

<br />
I imagined that the fire pet would be fine with root and snare and the like if we could choose it's spell list, but we would never get that.
<br />

<br />
I'm not too worried about the mana regen, though an increase for it would be nice. I think that the increase should come in the form of kindle. Kindle should be increased, and not by adding a new level 70 spell that nobody can get. the level 54 kindle will do fine if u are to increase the mana regen for the pet.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps the pet should only root or snare (I say snare because in the right hands snare is good) in defense of the master.
<br />

<br />
Just some ideas.<br />_________________<br />Summon an elemental and look at it. Thing is stacked, and that's a fact. It ain't holding nothing back, either.
<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecomendium.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Magician's Tower</a>: The best place for mages since the Plane of Sky!
<br />
--Faelolth Kepperofyarr, 56th Mage of Bertoxxulous, Freeborn Pirates</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
