			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The 51+ fire pets should be ranged nukers.  They should melee only if they are OOM and a mob is already within melee range.  Otherwise, when ordered to attack, they should move within range, then start nuking!
<br />

<br />
There's no reason for the pets to be identical to real wizzys.  After all, the earth pet isn't a true warrior (e.g., no defensive disc), so I see no reason for the fire pet to have 8 spell gems.  Ideally, the pet should cast an appropriate level nuke, perhaps a choice of fire, magic or cold based nukes that can be selected via /pet fire, /pet magic, or /pet cold commands.  These nukes should be mana-based.  When the pet goes OOM, it should resort to its innate FireElementalAttack (I think that's what it's called, can't find it on allakhazam.com at the moment) spell attack scaled to its level, the 63 fire pet should probably do 116 for its built-in fire-based spell attack.  The fire pet's mana-based nukes do not necessarily need to be real wizzy spells; this would probably work better for balance purposes (we should not be able to summon a 60 wizzy pet with full mana pool that does nothing but nuke; chaining such a pet would probably be a bit unbalancing).
<br />

<br />
This way the fire pet would provide ranged damage, unique among all pets (mage or otherwise).  The fire pet would have some sustained spell damage, which it would provide less sustained damage than the other pets' melee damage, but again, the benefit is that it's ranged damage.  Most of all, the fire pet would provide respectable burst damage but sustain it much longer if we reclaim and re-summon fire pets when they go OOM.
<br />

<br />
The fire pet should still DS itself, scaled to be proportional to the innate DS of its pre-50 predecessors.  This is primarily for tradition and also to avoid the embarassment of a pet that cons 60 being easily eaten alive by green mobs.
<br />

<br />
Of course the fire pet should *never* root, stun, ae, snare, dispel, or cast a useless wizzy ds.  Its nukes should, however, be lure-based and have a small resist modifier.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
