			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What about making the fire pet cast fire based lure spells.  Eliminate the melee.  Have it self buff with self rune spells, like diamondskin, manaskin etc.
<br />

<br />
Starting with the 52 fire pet, have it chain cast  <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1421&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enticement of Flame</a>
<br />

<br />
Then the 58 fire pet casts <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1638&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lure of Flame</a>
<br />

<br />

<br />
The 63 fire pet casts  <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3331&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Lure of Ro</a>
<br />

<br />
Maybe increase the casting times or recast times between the spells so as not to offend wizards.  Have the pet run LoM quickly if not.  I wouldn't think that the dps would be too great so as to be overpowering.  In fact it might be lower dps compared to the other pets.  With pet hold, they would likely be the preferred pet for raids where mobs have avoidable ae's, or AE rampage, and you wouldn't have to worry about your pet eatting enrage.  Pet backoff would cause the pet to duck and stop casting.  This seems to me to be keeping them more inline with their fire based origin (as opposed to ice comet) and would help their spells/procs to land on creatures that are higher level (raid) due to the resist mods on the spells i mentioned.   Also its a pet that can't be blamed for push on raids.  Which is a big reason that pets are sometimes not allowed on raid or can be harmful in a group in tight quarters.  This would also help on raids where things are very resistant to spells, this would help us stay with wizards in dps on these mobs, but still be relatively far behind as the pet would not have focus /aa's to crit.
<br />

<br />
Focusing the pet thru items would act as focii do for wizards, faster casts and/or improved damage items/chances to crit.  Also would allow for more versatility of our summoned focii items.(if they were deemed to be allowed to work on pet damage)  Just some thoughts, could likely use some refining/tuning.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
